    // Updated RealFace Content
    "case.realface.problem.title": "Problem: \"Real Face\" Issue in Online Dating",
    "case.realface.problem.desc": "Users cannot be sure that the people they meet online are real ‚Äî profiles often hide catfishing (using fake/stolen photos), AI-generated images, deepfakes, or fully synthetic personas created by scammers.<br><br><b>This leads to:</b><ul><li>Wasted time and emotional investment in fake relationships.</li><li>Financial losses from romance scams (money requests for \"emergencies\", investments, etc.).</li><li>Anxiety, distrust, and reduced willingness to use dating apps.</li></ul><br>In 2025‚Äì2026, generative AI has made fake profiles far more convincing ‚Äî photorealistic faces, real-time deepfake video calls, and automated chats fool even cautious users (reports show romance scams losses in hundreds of millions annually, with AI accelerating the problem).",
    
    "case.realface.solution.title": "How the project solves the \"Real Face\" problem",
    "case.realface.solution.desc": "The platform uses advanced AI-powered verification to analyze images and detect deception:<ul><li><b>AI-generated image detection</b> ‚Äî scans photos for signs of synthetic generation (artifacts from diffusion models, statistical anomalies, lack of natural inconsistencies).</li><li><b>Known scammer database check</b> ‚Äî cross-references faces against a growing internal blacklist of previously reported fraudsters or matched scam profiles.</li><li><b>Intervention flagging</b> ‚Äî identifies manipulations (deepfakes, face swaps, heavy edits) or stolen/recycled photos.</li></ul><p>By combining AI deepfake/synthetic detection with a scammer face database, the project creates a trust layer missing in most dating apps ‚Äî turning vague suspicion into actionable certainty and helping users focus on real connections instead of wasting resources on illusions.</p>",

