    "case.lovelang.caption": "Interactive Quiz ‚Äî Select an option to proceed",
    "case.lovelang.challenge.desc": "Translating the intangible concept of \"love languages\" into a tangible, digital experience. The goal was to create a warm, inviting interface that feels personal and safe without being overly cloying.",
    "case.lovelang.visual.desc": "I chose a soft palette of pinks and warm whites, paired with rounded typography to evoke gentleness. The card-based interaction mimics the feeling of playing a game or drawing a tarot card.",
    "case.lovelang.problem.title": "Problem üòî",
    "case.lovelang.problem.desc": "Partners often have different love languages (based on Gary Chapman's theory: Words of Affirmation, Quality Time, Receiving Gifts, Acts of Service, Physical Touch).<br><br>One person shows love through compliments and verbal encouragement, another through helping with chores or physical closeness, while a third values undivided attention and shared experiences.<br><br><b>When these styles don't match, it creates misunderstandings:</b><ul><li>‚ÄúI try so hard, but they don‚Äôt appreciate it!‚Äù</li><li>Feeling unloved even when love is being given ‚Äî just in the ‚Äúwrong‚Äù way.</li><li>Emotional distance, resentment, reduced intimacy, and a gradual decline in relationship satisfaction.</li><li>Over time: frustration, loneliness within the couple, frequent arguments, and even risk of breakup.</li></ul><p><b>The core pain for users:</b> ‚ÄúI love them, but I feel unloved,‚Äù ‚ÄúMy efforts don‚Äôt reach my partner,‚Äù ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre speaking different emotional languages ‚Äî and it‚Äôs damaging our connection.‚Äù</p>",
    "case.lovelang.solution.title": "Solution üí°",
    "case.lovelang.solution.desc": "Our app analyzes your partner‚Äôs current mood, preferences, and love language signals (through mood tracking, shared notes, message patterns, quick check-ins, interaction logs, and self-reported data). It then delivers highly personalized, real-time suggestions for actions that speak directly to their primary/current love language:<ul><li>‚ÄúYour partner is feeling low today ‚Äî send a heartfelt voice note with words of affirmation.‚Äù</li><li>‚ÄúThey‚Äôve had a stressful day ‚Äî plan a phone-free cozy evening together (Quality Time).‚Äù</li><li>‚ÄúActs of Service would mean the most right now ‚Äî surprise them by handling dinner or a small chore.‚Äù</li></ul><p>Daily gentle nudges, specific ideas, reminders, and progress tracking to help you consistently express love in the way that actually lands.</p>",
    "case.lovelang.benefits.title": "What users get",
    "case.lovelang.benefits.desc": "<ul><li><b>Deeper emotional connection</b> ‚Äî love is received and felt the way the partner truly needs it.</li><li><b>Far fewer misunderstandings</b> ‚Äî the app explains why ‚ÄúI‚Äôm trying, but it‚Äôs not working‚Äù and fixes it.</li><li><b>Warmer, more loving atmosphere</b> ‚Äî small, precise gestures build closeness, trust, and daily warmth.</li><li><b>Proactive relationship support</b> ‚Äî instead of guessing or fighting over ‚Äúwhy don‚Äôt you appreciate me?‚Äù, the app tells you exactly what works right now.</li></ul><p>Ultimately, the app transforms the classic ‚Äúmismatched love languages‚Äù problem into a superpower: you learn to speak your partner‚Äôs language fluently, making the relationship more harmonious, fulfilling, and resilient.</p>",
    // Quiz
