    // Learning Hub (Meddmax) Case
    "case.learninghub.next": "Next Project: RefillArena ‚Üí",
    "case.learninghub.caption": "Interactive Dashboard ‚Äî Click tabs to filter courses",
    "case.learninghub.overview.title": "Overview",
    "case.learninghub.overview.desc": "Learning Hub is an all-in-one platform for educational institutions. The main challenge was to design an interface that handles complex data (thousands of students and courses) without overwhelming the administrator.",
    "case.learninghub.design.title": "Design System",
    "case.learninghub.design.desc": "We used a clean, card-based layout with a purple accent color (#7C3AED) to evoke creativity and wisdom. The typography is set in Inter for maximum readability on data-heavy screens.",
    "case.learninghub.problem.title": "Problem üòî",
    "case.learninghub.problem.desc": "Teachers face overwhelming administrative burdens and fragmented tools in managing classrooms, leading to high workload, stress, and burnout.<br><b>Key pain points include:</b><ul><li>Spending excessive time on manual tasks like attendance tracking (hours weekly calling names or updating logs), grading assignments (often 9‚Äì10+ hours/week, taking work home), and compiling performance data.</li><li>Difficulty getting real-time, unified insights into student performance, attendance trends, engagement, and alerts (e.g., low grades, missing submissions, chronic absenteeism issues that surged post-pandemic and remain high in 2025‚Äì2026).</li><li>Juggling multiple disconnected systems (spreadsheets, separate apps for grading, attendance, communication), causing duplicated effort, delayed decisions, and missed opportunities to intervene early with struggling students.</li></ul><br><b>Resulting issues:</b> teacher fatigue, reduced time for actual teaching/lesson planning/student interaction, lower job satisfaction, and higher risk of leaving the profession amid ongoing challenges like chronic absenteeism (still ~23‚Äì28% in many districts) and student disengagement.<br>The core pain for teachers: <i>‚ÄúI‚Äôm drowning in admin work instead of teaching ‚Äî I don‚Äôt have quick visibility into who needs help, and everything feels scattered and time-consuming.‚Äù</i>",
    "case.learninghub.solution.title": "Solution üí°",
    "case.learninghub.solution.desc": "TeacherHub is an all-in-one teacher dashboard platform that centralizes classroom management, providing instant overviews and actionable insights in one intuitive interface (as shown in the screenshot: welcome dashboard with key metrics, course cards, alerts, etc.).<br>It integrates attendance, grading, student analytics, assignments, and alerts into a single view, allowing teachers like Ms. Sarah Thompson to:<ul><li><b>See at-a-glance stats</b> total students (e.g., 48), average attendance (92%), pending assignments (12 to grade), active alerts (4).</li><li><b>Monitor multiple courses</b> (Math 101A, Physics 202, etc.) with progress bars, student counts, and average grades.</li><li><b>Get real-time notifications</b> for issues (low attendance, at-risk students) to enable early interventions.</li><li><b>Streamline workflows</b> quick access to groups, students, assignments, and deeper analytics without switching tools.</li></ul>",
    "case.learninghub.benefits.title": "What teachers get",
    "case.learninghub.benefits.desc": "<ul><li><b>Significant time savings</b> ‚Äî automate/reduce manual tracking of attendance, grading queues, and data compilation (freeing hours weekly for teaching, planning, or personal time).</li><li><b>Better visibility & proactive support</b> ‚Äî unified dashboard reveals trends (e.g., attendance dips linked to performance) so teachers can address problems before they worsen, improving student outcomes and engagement.</li><li><b>Reduced stress & burnout</b> ‚Äî one centralized hub eliminates app overload and fragmented data, making daily management feel efficient and less overwhelming.</li><li><b>Enhanced focus on teaching</b> ‚Äî more energy for building relationships, personalizing instruction, and creating engaging lessons instead of paperwork.</li></ul>",
